01:30:35,515 --> 01:30:38,001
Meantime, back on Asgard,

1495
01:30:38,101 --> 01:30:42,188
Loki allows access for the Frost Giants.

1496
01:30:44,982 --> 01:30:49,095
And lonely Heimdall
looks to have been outwitted.

1497
01:30:49,195 --> 01:30:54,434
I'm sure that can't happen for long.
One feels his frustration in there,

1498
01:30:54,534 --> 01:30:57,770
and I certainly wouldn't want to try
and tie up Idris Elba

1499
01:30:57,870 --> 01:31:00,289
in any way that restricted him.

1500
01:31:01,874 --> 01:31:05,570
We shot these sequences
in the New Mexican desert,

1501
01:31:05,670 --> 01:31:08,339
and it was one of the areas

1502
01:31:09,006 --> 01:31:12,910
where it was so, so much
a signature of the picture

1503
01:31:13,010 --> 01:31:15,288
to see whether it would
work successfully

1504
01:31:15,388 --> 01:31:19,542
to put these costumes
from these Asgardians on Earth.

1505
01:31:19,642 --> 01:31:22,128
And in that space of the desert,
on that kind of canvas,

1506
01:31:22,228 --> 01:31:25,064
I was very, very pleased with the results.

1507
01:31:27,400 --> 01:31:29,844
So, to see them there,
there's something, I don't know,

1508
01:31:29,944 --> 01:31:33,806
very, very much in tune with
modern versions of the comic books.

1509
01:31:33,906 --> 01:31:35,975
Particularly, for instance,
runs of the comics

1510
01:31:36,075 --> 01:31:39,062
that had been authored
by Joe Michael Straczynski,

1511
01:31:39,162 --> 01:31:44,750
who, in a way, was part of perfecting
the modern version of Thor on Earth.

1512
01:31:49,422 --> 01:31:53,342
Heimdall is heroic and allows us

1513
01:31:54,135 --> 01:31:59,123
to just see what we can play,
of the extent to which

1514
01:31:59,223 --> 01:32:04,045
this romantic feeling between
Thor and Jane can play in the movie.

1515
01:32:04,145 --> 01:32:06,005
And I think it's a tribute to these two

1516
01:32:06,105 --> 01:32:09,175
that it carries much more weight
than it might otherwise do

1517
01:32:09,275 --> 01:32:12,678
because of its gentleness
and its simplicity.

1518
01:32:12,778 --> 01:32:13,971
It doesn't strain too hard,

1519
01:32:14,071 --> 01:32:19,185
they don't strain too hard to be
super sexy, super cool, super romantic.

1520
01:32:19,285 --> 01:32:22,438
As a result, I think
that they are all of those things,

1521
01:32:22,538 --> 01:32:24,690
and I think we want them to be together.

1522
01:32:24,790 --> 01:32:28,986
We know that this hasn't progressed
into the grand love affair,

1523
01:32:29,086 --> 01:32:32,990
but we see that it has the potential
for perhaps something very special

1524
01:32:33,090 --> 01:32:35,468
and that there is a connection.

1525
01:32:41,974 --> 01:32:45,545
Now, we head into
the final phase of the film.

1526
01:32:45,645 --> 01:32:50,316
We're back on Asgard, and the family
business has to be taken care of.

1527
01:32:53,319 --> 01:32:55,596
First of all, of course,
we give Frigga a moment

1528
01:32:55,696 --> 01:33:00,143
to do what any warrior queen would do,
which is to try and defend her husband.

1529
01:33:00,243 --> 01:33:03,479
We consciously kept
the world of Asgard, these corridors,

1530
01:33:03,579 --> 01:33:06,107
a little emptier
